    </div>
    <div class="sixteen columns intro-text">
        <p>
        Shinpachi is a cool little tool that can help you to debug
        network protocols and APIs, especially HTTP and REST APIs.
        It's built for the web, and with web technologies.
        </p>
        <p>
        In short, Shinpachi is basically a
        <a href="https://www.wireshark.org/">Wireshark</a> that can
        be plugged in between your client and server as a proxy server.
        </p>
        <p>
        To use Shinpachi, all you need is a recent web browser. It's
        easy to set up, and most operating systems and smart devices
        are supported.
        </p>
        <div class="misc-buttons">
            <a class="big-button start-button wow bounceInUp" href="/">Start Using It Now</a>
        </div>
        <div class="misc-buttons">
            <a class="big-button usage-button wow bounceInUp" href="#usage">Usage</a>
            <a class="big-button usage-button wow bounceInUp" href="#faq">F.A.Q.</a>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sixteen columns">
        <hr class="intro-hr" />
    </div>
    <div class="eight columns intro-text wow bounceInUp" data-wow-offset="100">
        <p>
        It's Based on the widely accepted HTTP proxy protocol.
        TCP streams from given devices and software can be captured
        with ease as long as they support HTTP proxies.
        </p>
    </div>
