    <div class="sixteen columns">
        <h1 class="intro-title" id="usage">Usage</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="sixteen columns">
        <ol class="usage-steps">
            <li>
                <p>
                To use Shinpachi's console, you need to sign in first.
                This requirement for signing in is for preventing
                malicious use of Shinpachi's proxy server, but no
                personal account data will be stored in our server.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                In the console, subscribe to the endpoint(s) you want to
                listen to.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <img src="static/img/usage-subscribe.png" alt="Subscription Panel" />
                </p>
                <p>
                The subscriptions work in two ways. If you subscribed to
                only one endpoint, all streams connected to that endpoint
                would be captured, no matter what the other end is. And
                if you subscribed to two endpoints, only streams between
                those endpoints would be captured.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                Point your client's HTTP proxy to the address and port
                presented by the console.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                Make requests in your client as usual. Now you can examine
                the communications in Shinpachi's console.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <img src="static/img/usage-console.png" alt="Captured Data" />
                </p>
                <p class="note">
                Note that, to allow your client to make requests through
                Shinpachi, you must make a subscription to your client's
                endpoint first.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="sixteen columns">
