    </div>
    <div class="sixteen columns">
        <h1 class="intro-title" id="faq">F.A.Q.</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="sixteen columns">
        <ol class="faq-list">
            <li>
                <p>
                Q: The HTTP proxy server returned code 403, why?
                </p>
                <p>
                A: Only the IPs subscribed to in Shinpachi's console will have access to the proxy server.
                If you want a device to use the proxy server, subscribe to the device's IP first.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                Q: Why can't I receive any captured data in the console?
                </p>
                <p>
                A: Despite of network problems and natural disasters like an erupting volcano,
                here's a checklist.
                </p>
                <ul class="checklist">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                        Make sure you subscribed to the public IP of your device/browser that you wanted
                        to listen to. Private IPs like 192.168.*.* and 10.*.*.* won't work. You can use
                        <a href="http://ifconfig.me">ifconfig.me</a> to determine your public IP.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                        If you subscribed to two endpoints in one subscription, you can only see the activities
                        between those two endpoints. Make sure those two endpoints are the correct ones. You can
                        inspect the subscriptions by clicking the "Subscriptions" button in the console, or by
                        pressing the "L" key.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                        Shinpachi can only handle TCP streams, so streams of other protocols, such as UDP, won't
                        show up in the console.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                Q: Does Shinpachi support IPv6?
                </p>
                <p>
                A: Yes. You can subscribe to IPv6 addresses, as long as your network supports IPv6 too.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                Q: There are some replies in TCP streams that are missing or incomplete, why's that?
                </p>
                <p>
                A: To maximize performance, Shinpachi uses an asynchronous trigger mechanism to handle
                subscriptions. If you subscribed to only one endpoint in a subscription, the proxy server
                will learn about other endpoints only when the original endpoint talks to the others.
                Some data may get dropped during the learning process, but all data will be captured once
                all endpoints are learnt about. On the other hand, if you subscribed to two endpoints in
                one subscription, the server knows about all the endpoints, so no data will get dropped.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                Q: I have tons of other questions.
                </p>
                <p>
                A: Please, <a href="mailto:l04m33@gmail.com">drop me a line</a>, or leave a comment
                in the <a href="#disqus_thread">comments section</a> at the bottom of this page.
                You can also do these even if you have no real questions. I don't mind :).
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
